</div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <a href="Mississippi_River" title="Mississippi River">Mississippi</a> was opened to Union traffic to the southern border of Tennessee with the taking of <a href="Battle_of_Island_Number_Ten" title="Battle of Island Number Ten">Island No. 10</a> and <a href="New_Madrid,_Missouri" title="New Madrid, Missouri">New Madrid</a>, Missouri, and then <a href="Memphis,_Tennessee" title="Memphis, Tennessee">Memphis, Tennessee</a>. In April 1862, the <a href="Union_Navy" title="Union Navy">Union Navy</a> captured New Orleans,<sup id="cite_ref-mcpherson49_167-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mcpherson49-167"><span>[</span>167<span>]</span></a></sup> which allowed Union forces to begin moving up the Mississippi. Only the fortress city of <a href="Vicksburg,_Mississippi" title="Vicksburg, Mississippi">Vicksburg</a>, Mississippi, prevented Union control of the entire river.</p>
<p>General <a href="Braxton_Bragg" title="Braxton Bragg">Braxton Bragg</a>'s second Confederate invasion of Kentucky ended with a meaningless victory over Maj. Gen. <a href="Don_Carlos_Buell" title="Don Carlos Buell">Don Carlos Buell</a> at the <a href="Battle_of_Perryville" title="Battle of Perryville">Battle of Perryville</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-mcpherson50_168-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mcpherson50-168"><span>[</span>168<span>]</span></a></sup> although Bragg was forced to end his attempt at invading Kentucky and retreat due to lack of support for the Confederacy in that state. Bragg was narrowly defeated by Maj. Gen. <a href="William_Rosecrans" title="William Rosecrans">William Rosecrans</a> at the <a href="Battle_of_Stones_River" title="Battle of Stones River">Battle of Stones River</a><sup id="cite_ref-mcpherson51_169-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mcpherson51-169"><span>[</span>169<span>]</span></a></sup> in <a href="Tennessee" title="Tennessee">Tennessee</a>.</p>
<p>The one clear Confederate victory in the West was the <a href="Battle_of_Chickamauga" title="Battle of Chickamauga">Battle of Chickamauga</a>. Bragg, reinforced by Lt. Gen. <a href="James_Longstreet" title="James Longstreet">James Longstreet</a>'s corps (from Lee's army in the east), defeated Rosecrans, despite the heroic defensive stand of Maj. Gen. <a href="George_Henry_Thomas" title="George Henry Thomas">George Henry Thomas</a>. Rosecrans retreated to <a href="Chattanooga,_Tennessee" title="Chattanooga, Tennessee">Chattanooga</a>, which Bragg then besieged.</p>
<p>The Union's key strategist and tactician in the West was <a href="../Ulysses_S._Grant" title="Ulysses S. Grant">Ulysses S. Grant</a>, who won victories at Forts <a href="Battle_of_Fort_Henry" title="Battle of Fort Henry">Henry</a> and <a href="Battle_of_Fort_Donelson" title="Battle of Fort Donelson">Donelson</a> (by which the Union seized control of the <a href="Tennessee_River" title="Tennessee River">Tennessee</a> and <a href="Cumberland_River" title="Cumberland River">Cumberland</a> Rivers); <a href="Battle_of_Shiloh" title="Battle of Shiloh">the Battle of Shiloh</a>;<sup id="cite_ref-mcpherson52_170-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mcpherson52-170"><span>[</span>170<span>]</span></a></sup> and the <a href="Siege_of_Vicksburg" title="Siege of Vicksburg">Battle of Vicksburg</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-mcpherson53_171-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mcpherson53-171"><span>[</span>171<span>]</span></a></sup> which cemented Union control of the Mississippi River and is considered one of the <a href="Turning_point_of_the_American_Civil_War" title="Turning point of the American Civil War">turning points</a> of the war. Grant marched to the relief of Rosecrans and defeated Bragg at the <a href="Chattanooga_Campaign" title="Chattanooga Campaign">Third Battle of Chattanooga</a>,<sup id="cite_ref-mcpherson54_172-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-mcpherson54-172"><span>[</span>172<span>]</span></a></sup> driving Confederate forces out of Tennessee and opening a route to Atlanta and the heart of the Confederacy.</p>
<h3> <span class="mw-headline" id="Trans-Mississippi">Trans-Mississippi</span></h3>
<div class="rellink boilerplate seealso">For more details on Missouri in the Civil War, see <a href="Trans-Mississippi_Theater_of_the_American_Civil_War" title="Trans-Mississippi Theater of the American Civil War">Trans-Mississippi Theater of the American Civil War</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:448px;">
<table style="background: transparent; border: 0; padding: 0; margin: 0; width:444px;" cellspacing="0">
<tr style="vertical-align:middle;">
<td style="padding: auto; margin: 0;" class="thumbimage"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Battle_of_Lawrence.png" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9b/Battle_of_Lawrence.png/220px-Battle_of_Lawrence.png" width="220" height="143" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9b/Battle_of_Lawrence.png/330px-Battle_of_Lawrence.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9b/Battle_of_Lawrence.png/440px-Battle_of_Lawrence.png 2x" /></a></td>
<td style="padding: 0; margin: 0; border: 0; width: 2px"></td>
<td style="padding: auto; margin: 0;" class="thumbimage"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Wilson's_Creek_charge_of_1st_Iowa.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Wilson's_Creek_charge_of_1st_Iowa.jpg/220px-Wilson's_Creek_charge_of_1st_Iowa.jpg" width="220" height="141" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Wilson%27s_Creek_charge_of_1st_Iowa.jpg/330px-Wilson%27s_Creek_charge_of_1st_Iowa.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Wilson%27s_Creek_charge_of_1st_Iowa.jpg/440px-Wilson%27s_Creek_charge_of_1st_Iowa.jpg 2x" /></a></td>
</tr>
<tr style="vertical-align:top;">
<td style="padding: 0; margin: 0; border: 0;">
<div class="thumbcaption">
